msgstr "Yleiskatsaus skannattavista vastaanotoista."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:92
msgid ""
"To process and scan each product individually, scan a product or product "
"packaging, or choose a specific product line. Click the :guilabel:`+#` "
"button (for example, `+10`) to indicate receipt of that product."
msgstr ""
"Käsittele ja skannaa jokainen tuote erikseen skannaamalla tuote tai "
"tuotepakkaus tai valitsemalla tietty tuoterivi. Napsauta :guilabel:`+#`-"
"painiketta (esimerkiksi `+10`) ilmoittaaksesi kyseisen tuotteen "
"vastaanottamisesta."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:97
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:171
msgid "Editing a product line"
msgstr "Tuoterivin muokkaus"

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:99
msgid ""
"To manually adjust received quantities for a product, click the :icon:`fa-"
"pencil` :guilabel:`(pencil)` icon to open a new screen to edit that product "
"line."
msgstr ""
"Muokkaa tuotteen vastaanotettuja määriä manuaalisesti napsauttamalla "
":icon:`fa-pencil` :guilabel:`(kynä)`-kuvaketta avataksesi uuden näytön "
"kyseisen tuoterivin muokkaamiseksi."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:102
msgid ""
"On this screen, the product that's being received is listed. Under the "
"product name, edit the :guilabel:`Quantity` line. Change the `0` in the line "
"to the desired quantity, or click the :guilabel:`/# Units` button (for "
"example, `/12 Units`) to automatically fill the quantity ordered from the |"
"PO|."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:107
msgid ""
"Additionally, click the :guilabel:`+1` and :guilabel:`-1` buttons to add or "
"subtract quantity of the product. Click the :guilabel:`+# Units` button to "
"add a product packaging. Click the number keys to add quantity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:111
msgid ""
"Below the number keys is the :guilabel:`Location` line, which reads `WH/"
"Stock` by default, unless another *location* is listed on the product "
"itself. Click this line to reveal a drop-down menu of additional locations "
"to choose from."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:115
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:192
msgid ""
"When ready, click :guilabel:`Confirm` to confirm the changes made to the "
"product line."
msgstr ""
"Kun olet valmis, vahvista tuoteriville tehdyt muutokset napsauttamalla "
":guilabel:`Vahvista`."

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:118
msgid ""
"In the reception operation `WH/IN/00012`, `12 Units` of `Soda Can` are "
"expected to be received. Warehouse employees can scan the barcode of the "
"`Soda Can` product to receive one unit, or because they can be purchased in "
"6-pack packaging, they can scan the packaging barcode. Alternatively, they "
"can click the :icon:`fa-pencil` :guilabel:`(pencil)` icon to manually enter "
"the received quantities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/receipts_deliveries.rst:0
#: ../../content/applications/inventory_and_mrp/barcode/operations/transfers_scratch.rst:0
